result.name: Genetic and pathogenic diversity among isolates of Diaporthe helianthi causing Phomopsis stem canker disease on sunflower.
result.description: Population genetic and pathogenic diversity studies of Diaporthe helianthi isolates collected from the major U.S. sunflower growing regions of Minnesota, North Dakota, and South Dakota.
result.center: USDA-ARS Edward T. Schafer Agricultural Research Center
